    "rationale": "This is a classic and simple example of the Hofmann-Löffler-Freytag reaction. N-chloro-N-methylbutylamine undergoes a 1,5-hydrogen atom transfer via a nitrogen-centered radical, generated under acidic conditions (often with light or heat). The resulting carbon-centered radical then abstracts the chlorine atom, forming a \u03b4-chloroamine. Subsequent intramolecular nucleophilic substitution, typically induced by a base (often implicitly present or added, like water acting as a base after protonation), leads to the formation of the five-membered N-methylpyrrolidine ring.",
    "collision_avoidance_note": "The reaction involves an N-haloamine substrate and the formation of a pyrrolidine ring via an intramolecular C-H functionalization. This specific transformation (N-haloamine to pyrrolidine) is characteristic of the Hofmann-Löffler-Freytag reaction and avoids common motifs like arenes, diazo groups, or decarboxylations that could cause collisions with other named reactions. The acyclic starting material and simple alkyl groups keep the example focused on the core transformation."
